foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: 3 requests received after FY14 were backdated with FY14 received dates. The 3 requests were updated to reflect correct received dates, which resulted in 3 less requests pending for FY14.

The discrepancy in the number of pending requests is due to how cases are tracked within our case management system. Example: a request initially assigned to Office "A" in FY14 is later assigned to Office "B" would show as a pending case for Office "A" at the end of FY14, but when Office "B" closes the case in FY15, the report will show Office "B" as the pending office at the start of FY15 rather than Office "A".
